read_jsonl[source]

read_jsonl(file_path)

Read a .jsonl file and yield its contents line by line. file_path (unicode / Path): The file path. YIELDS: The loaded JSON contents of each line.

rj = read_jsonl('test_data/sample.jsonl')
data_point = next(rj)
assert 'image' in data_point, 'image key expected'
assert 'width' in data_point, 'width key expected'
assert 'height' in data_point, 'height key expected'
assert 'spans' in data_point, 'spans key expected'

base64ToImage[source]

base64ToImage(base64_string)

convert base64 string to image

rj = read_jsonl('test_data/sample.jsonl')
data_point = next(rj)
image = base64ToImage(data_point['image'])
assert type(image) == Image, 'fastai.vision.image.Image type expected'
assert image.size == torch.Size([352, 640])
image

get_bbox_coordinates[source]

get_bbox_coordinates(points:list)

converts points from json file to fastai boxes points

get_bbox_from_spans[source]

get_bbox_from_spans(height, width, spans)

gets fastai bbox object from spans entry

rj = read_jsonl('test_data/sample.jsonl')
data_point = 0

#find entry with more than one bounding box
for data in rj:
    if len(data['spans']) > 1:
        data_point = data
        break
        
image = base64ToImage(data_point['image'])
boxes = [get_bbox_coordinates(data_point['spans'][0]['points'])]
assert boxes == [[30.3, 172.4, 145.6, 303.8]]

bbox = get_bbox_from_spans(*image.size, data_point['spans'])
